Pseudobithynia pentheri is a species of freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum, an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Bithyniidae.
The specific name pentheri is in honor of malacologist Arnold Penther, who collected this species.Gl√∂er & Yildrim (2006) moved this species from the genus Bythinia to the genus Pseudobithynia in 2006.